title: Air bike
desc: This workout focuses on your legs and cardiovascular health. You'll ride an air bike for 30 minutes at a moderate pace, then increase the resistance for 5 minutes to challenge yourself. Repeat this process for a total of 45 minutes.

title: Bench Dip (knees bent)
desc: Perform dips from a bench with knees bent, targeting triceps and chest muscles.

title: Bridge (straight arm)
desc: Perform a bridge exercise with straight arms, targeting the glutes and hamstrings. Hold for a brief moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower back down to the starting position.

title: Chest Dip
desc: Perform dips by hanging from a bar with your hands shoulder-width apart. Lower your body until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle, then straighten them to return to the starting position.

title: Circles Arm
desc: Perform bicep curls and tricep extensions while moving in a circle with your arms. For beginners, perform 5-10 reps or sets of the exercise.

title: Circles Elbow Arm
desc: Hold a dumbbell in each hand and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Move your arms in circular motions, keeping your upper arms still, to target the muscles of your upper arm. Do 10 reps for 5 sets.

title: Cross Jacks
desc: Perform jumping jacks while holding a medicine ball in each hand. Keep your core engaged and switch arms after each rep.

title: Dead Bug
desc: Perform a dead bug exercise by lying on your back and raising both legs and arms off the ground, holding for 10-15 seconds and repeating for 3 sets.

title: Donkey Calf Raise
desc: Stand on a step or platform with your feet shoulder-width apart. Slowly raise up onto tiptoes, then lower back down. This exercise targets the calf muscles and can help improve balance and stability.

title: Dynamic Chest Stretch
desc: Stretch your chest muscles using dynamic movements like arm circles and shoulder rolls. Perform 5-10 reps or 3-5 sets

title: Elbows Back Stretch
desc: Stretches the muscles in the upper back and improves flexibility.

title: Flutter Kicks
desc: Flutter kicks are a great exercise for your legs and core. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, then lift one leg off the ground and hold it in mid-air for 2-3 seconds before lowering it back down. Repeat on the other side. Do 10 reps on each leg.

title: Frog Squat
desc: Female Frog Squats for Beginners

title: Front and Back Neck Stretch
desc: Perform a slow neck stretch in both front and back positions. Hold each position for 30 seconds.

title: Gorilla Chin
desc: This workout focuses on building strength and endurance in the chest muscles. It involves 3 sets of 10 reps of push-ups, followed by 3 sets of 12 reps of dumbbell rows, and finishes with a set of 15 reps of plank holds.

title: Hanging Leg Raise
desc: Perform 10 reps of hanging leg raises on each leg, rest for 30 seconds in between sets.

title: Incline Push Up Depth Jump
desc: Perform incline push-ups with a depth jump at the top of each rep. Aim for 3 sets of 12 reps.

title: Inverted Row
desc: Perform inverted rows by hanging from a bar with hands shoulder-width apart. Lower your body until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle, then pull yourself back up to the starting position.

title: Isometric Wipers
desc: This exercise targets the muscles in your upper back and shoulders. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a light dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. Keeping your arms straight, lift one dumbbell towards your opposite ear, then lower it back down to the starting position. Repeat on the other side.

title: Jack Burpee
desc: Perform a set of 10 burpees followed by a set of 20 jump squats. Repeat for 3 sets.

duration.desc: Each set should take around 1-2 minutes

title: Jack knife Floor
desc: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Lift shoulders off the ground, straighten arms, then lower back down.

title: Jack Step
desc: A beginner-level workout that involves step-ups and jumping jacks.

title: Jump Box
desc: This intermediate-level workout involves jumping and plyometric exercises to improve strength, endurance, and agility. It should be done for 10-15 minutes.

title: Kipping Muscle Up
desc: This exercise combines a pull-up with a kipping motion, targeting the muscles of the back, arms, and core. It is considered an advanced exercise and should only be performed by those with a good level of strength and control.

title: Kneeling Hip Flexor
desc: Lie on your hands and knees, bringing one knee towards the chest while keeping the other foot flat on the ground. Alternate legs with each rep.

title: Kneeling Wrist Flexor Stretch
desc: Stand on one knee with the other foot in front of you. Hold onto something stable for balance. Keeping your upper arm still, bend your elbow and flex your wrist downward.

title: Lateral Speed Step
desc: Perform lateral steps on a step platform with your feet shoulder-width apart. Increase the speed and intensity of the steps as you continue.

title: Lying Scissor Crunch
desc: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Lift shoulders off the ground, bringing left elbow to right knee as you straighten left leg. Lower back down and repeat on other side. Do 15 reps.

title: March Sit (wall)
desc: Perform a wall march for 30 seconds, alternating arms and legs, for a total of 15-20 minutes.

title: Neck Bridge Prone
desc: Perform neck bridges in a prone position to strengthen your upper back and improve posture.

title: One Arm Dip
desc: Perform dips with one arm while holding onto a stable object or bench with the other hand. Start with a beginner level and gradually increase the reps and sets as you build strength.

title: Overhead Triceps Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a light dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. Keeping your upper arms still, bend your elbows to stretch your triceps.

title: Plyo Side Lunge Stretch
desc: This exercise targets the legs and hips. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, then step forward with one foot and lower your body until your back knee almost touches the ground.

title: Pull up (neutral grip)
desc: Perform as many pull-ups as possible in 1 minute. Aim to increase reps each week.

title: Ring Dips
desc: Perform ring dips by hanging from a pull-up bar with your hands shoulder-width apart. Lower your body until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle, then lift back up to the starting position.

title: Run
desc: Do 3 sets of 5-10 minute runs. Rest for 2-3 minutes in between each set.

title: Russian Twist
desc: Perform twists on a stability ball while lying on your back. Use a slow and controlled motion to target your obliques.

title: Seated Lower Back Stretch
desc: Sit on a mat or chair with feet flat on the floor and knees bent. Lean forward slowly and hold for 30 seconds to stretch your lower back. Repeat 5 times.

title: Seated Single Leg Hamstring Stretch
desc: Sit on the floor with one leg extended in front of you and the other foot resting on the ground. Lean forward and stretch your hamstring. Hold for 30 seconds to a minute and repeat on the other side.

title: Side Bridge (bent knee)
desc: Lie on your side with bent knees and lift feet off ground, hold for 30 seconds

title: Side Bridge Hip Abduction (star)
desc: Perform side bridges while abducting your hips. Lie on your side with knees bent and feet flat, then lift your hips off the ground while keeping your feet in place.

title: Side Push Neck Stretch
desc: Stretches the muscles on one side of the neck and shoulders to relieve tension and improve range of motion.

title: Single Leg Bridge
desc: Lie on your back with both knees bent and feet flat on the ground. Lift one leg off the ground, keeping it straight, then lower it back down without touching the ground. Repeat with the other leg.

title: Single Leg Platform Slide
desc: Lie on a platform on your back with one leg extended and the other bent. Slowly slide the bent leg out to the side, keeping it straight, then lower it back down to the starting position.

title: Sit (wall)
desc: Sit on a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back against the wall. Hold for 30 seconds to a minute.

title: Slopes Towards Stretch
desc: This workout should be done for 5-10 minutes, with a focus on gentle stretching and light cardio on a slope. Beginners can start with shorter intervals and gradually increase the duration as they become more comfortable.

title: Split Jacks
desc: Perform rapid foot alternations while keeping your legs straight, targeting the lower body muscles.

title: Squat (arms overhead)
desc: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, then bend knees and lower body weight down until thighs are parallel to ground. Raise arms overhead.

title: Squat Jacks
desc: A high-intensity interval workout that involves jumping squats. Great for burning calories and improving cardiovascular health.

title: Squat
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, then bend your knees and lower your body down until your thighs are parallel to the ground. Push back up to the starting position.

title: Standing Hamstring Stretch
desc: This workout involves standing on one leg and bending the other knee to stretch the hamstrings. Perform 3 sets of 10 reps on each leg.

title: Star Jump
desc: Perform a set of 10-15 jumping jacks, alternating legs with each rep. Rest for 30 seconds before repeating.

title: Triceps Dips Floor
desc: Perform dips on the floor with your hands grasping a bar or dumbbells. Start in a seated position with your feet flat on the ground and slowly lower your body weight by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. Push back up to the starting position and repeat for 10-15 reps, resting as needed between sets.

title: Triceps Press
desc: Perform triceps presses using dumbbells or barbell with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lower the weight to your sides and press it back up to the starting position.

title: Vertical Mountain Climber
desc: This exercise targets your core and legs by having you climb up a virtual mountain. Your goal is to reach the top of the mountain as quickly as possible while maintaining proper form.

title: Wind Sprints
desc: This workout involves sprinting in a windy environment. it's important to dress appropriately for the weather and stay hydrated throughout the exercise.

title: Reverse plank
desc: Hold a reverse plank position for 30-60 seconds. Start in a plank position with your feet hip-width apart and your hands shoulder-width apart, then slowly lower your body until your forearms are resting on the ground and your elbows are bent at a 90-degree angle.

title: 45 degree hyperextension (arms in front of chest)
desc: Lie on your back with arms extended straight out in front of you. Slowly lift arms upwards until they are at a 45-degree angle to your body.

title: Bridge Pose Setu Bandhasana
desc: Perform the bridge pose while engaging your core and bandhasana muscles. This exercise helps to strengthen your back, glutes, and hamstrings.

title: Child Pose
desc: This exercise should be done for 5-10 minutes or 3-5 sets of 10 reps each. As a beginner, you should focus on proper form and control throughout the movement.

title: Crane Pose Bakasana
desc: Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground, stretching your arms overhead. For beginners, hold for 30 seconds to a minute.

title: Downward Facing Dog Adho Mukha Svanasana
desc: This exercise is great for beginners as it helps to strengthen the arms and legs while improving flexibility and balance. It also helps to open up the chest and shoulders.

title: Fish Pose Matsyasana
desc: Lie on your back with arms and legs fully extended. Inhale and lift your legs and chest, arching your back. Exhale and gently lower your legs and head to the floor.

title: Garland Pose Malasana
desc: This pose strengthens your core and legs while improving balance and flexibility.

title: Hands to Feet Pada Hastasana
desc: A gentle flowing sequence that strengthens the core and opens the hips.

title: Hero Pose Virasana
desc: This exercise should be done for 5-10 minutes, 3-5 sets.

title: Revolved Side Angle Pose Parivrtta Parsvakonasana
desc: This pose should be held for 5-10 minutes, focusing on proper alignment and breath. Beginners can start with shorter holds and gradually increase the time as they build strength and flexibility.

title: Standing Forward Bend Uttanasana
desc: Standing forward bend uttanasana is a beginner level yoga pose that can help relieve stress and tension in the back and hips. Hold the pose for 5-10 minutes, breathing deeply and focusing on your breath.

title: Stand Spread Leg Forward Fold
desc: Perform a standing forward fold while keeping your legs straight and spread apart. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat for 5-7 sets.

title: Tree Pose Vrksasana
desc: Stand on one leg, with the other foot resting on the inner thigh. Keep your spine straight and your arms by your sides.

title: Triangle Pose Trikonasana
desc: Stand with your feet hip-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and reach for your hips, stretching your arms overhead and interlacing your fingers. Keep your spine long and engaged.

title: Warrior Pose I Virabhadrasana I
desc: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, then bend your right knee and stretch your arms out to the sides. Balance on your left leg.

title: Wide legged Forward Bend Prasarita Padottanasana
desc: Stretches the hamstrings, calves, and spine. Helps in relieving stress and fatigue.

title: One leg kickback (with bench support)
desc: Perform a kickback exercise with one leg while sitting on a bench. Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. Lift one leg off the bench, keeping it straight, and hold for 2 seconds before lowering it back down to the starting position. Repeat for 10 reps, rest for 30 seconds, and repeat for 5 minutes.

title: Lunging Straight Leg Calf Stretch
desc: Perform a lunge with one leg while the other leg is stretched out in front of you. Hold for 30-60 seconds and then switch legs.

title: 45 degree one leg hyperextension (arms in front of chest)
desc: Lie on your back with one leg extended and the other bent at a 45-degree angle. Lower your body down towards the ground by straightening your bent knee, then push back up to the starting position.

title: 45 degree twisting hyperextension
desc: This exercise targets the hamstrings, glutes and lower back muscles. It also improves flexibility and range of motion in the hips and legs.

title: Lying Simultaneous Alternating Straight Leg Raise
desc: Perform simultaneous alternating straight leg raises on your back while lying down. This exercise targets the hamstrings, glutes and core muscles.

title: Dead Bug (version 2)
desc: Perform a dead bug move with both legs, then switch and repeat on the other side.

title: Hollow Hold
desc: Hold a hollow body position for 30-60 seconds. Engage your core and maintain proper form throughout the hold.

title: Plyo Push Up
desc: Perform a set of push ups with added explosive jump at the top

title: Weighted Drop Push Up
desc: Perform push ups with a weight on your chest. Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels and lower yourself until your chest nearly touches the ground, then push back up.

title: Wide Hand Push up
desc: Perform push-ups with your hands shoulder-width apart and focus on proper form. This exercise targets the chest muscles and helps improve overall upper body strength.

title: Spine Stretch
desc: This exercise stretches the spine and helps to improve flexibility. It can be done standing or sitting.

title: Ankle Circles
desc: Helps to improve balance and strength in the ankles. Stand on one leg while holding onto something stable for support. Slowly circle your ankle in a circular motion, first clockwise and then counterclockwise.

title: Bodyweight Standing Calf Raise
desc: Perform calf raises on a standing position using your body weight. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, then raise up onto your tiptoes and lower back down. Do 5-10 reps in 3 sets.

title: Calf Stretch With Hands Against Wall
desc: Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. Slowly lower yourself down into a seated position, keeping your heels on the ground and your arms extended overhead. Hold for 30 seconds and then stand up slowly.

title: One Leg Floor Calf Raise
desc: Perform calf raises on one leg at a time, alternating legs with each rep.

title: L-sit
desc: Perform L-sits for 30 seconds, rest for 1 minute and repeat for 3 sets.

title: Neck Side Stretch
desc: Stretches the muscles on one side of the neck to relieve tension and improve flexibility.

title: Pelvic Tilt Into Bridge
desc: Targets hamstrings, glutes, and lower back muscles. Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the ground, then lift pelvis and upper back off the floor, keeping shoulders down and away from ears. Lower back slowly to starting position

title: Reverse Hyper on Flat Bench
desc: Perform reverse hyper on a flat bench with proper form. Keep your core engaged and lower your body until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle.

title: Straight Leg Outer Hip Abductor
desc: Targets the outer hip muscles through a dynamic movement that requires engagement of the core and glutes. Perform on a straight leg with feet hip-width apart, lift the leg outward and hold for 2 seconds before lowering back down.

title: Wrist Circles
desc: Hold your arms straight out to the sides and make small circles with your wrists for 5-10 reps

title: Plank arm lifts
desc: Perform a plank position while lifting arms in and out. Female.

title: Barbell Full Squat (Back POV)
desc: Perform full squats with barbell, focusing on proper form and depth. Start with 3 sets of 8-12 reps for both legs.

duration.desc: 3 sets of 8-12 reps for both legs

title: Lateral Side Plank
desc: Hold a side plank on the lateral (side) of your body for 30 seconds. This exercise targets the core muscles, obliques and lower back.

title: Inchworm
desc: Perform the exercise in a straight line with each rep, keeping your back straight and core engaged. Do 5-10 reps for 5-10 minutes.

title: Forward Jump
desc: Perform a series of jumping jacks facing forward, landing softly on the balls of your feet and immediately jumping up again. Repeat for 30 seconds.

title: Locust Yoga Pose (Iron Man Pose)
desc: This yoga pose strengthens your core and improves flexibility. Get into a plank position, then lift your right arm and left leg off the ground, holding for 5-10 breaths before switching sides.

title: Plow Yoga Pose
desc: Plow Pose is a beginner-level yoga pose that helps to stretch the chest and improve posture.

title: Triceps Dip Stretch
desc: Perform triceps dips by placing your hands on a bench or chair and lowering your body weight down and back up. Hold for 2-3 seconds, repeat for 10-15 reps.

title: Oblique Crunch (Version 2)
desc: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place hands behind head for support.

title: Intermediate Hip Flexor and Quad Stretch
desc: This workout should be done for 10-15 minutes, focusing on deep stretching and holding each pose for 30 seconds to 1 minute. It is recommended for individuals who have experienced some level of strength training and are looking to improve their flexibility and range of motion.

title: Leg Up Hamstring Stretch
desc: Stand on one leg and slowly lift the other leg, keeping it straight. Hold for 2-3 seconds before lowering back down.

title: Prisoner Squat
desc: Perform squats while handcuffed to a bar. Hold for 20 seconds before switching sides.

title: Bodyweight Rear Lunge
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps for each leg, resting for 30 seconds in between sets.

title: Rocket Jump
desc: Perform a series of jumping jacks, landing softly on the balls of your feet and immediately jumping back up to the starting position. Repeat for 30 seconds.

title: Single Leg Push Off
desc: Perform a single leg push off by standing on one leg and pushing off the ground with the other leg. Repeat for 30 seconds, then switch legs.

title: Standing Long Jump
desc: Perform standing long jumps at maximum height, aiming to beat your previous record. This exercise is best suited for experts as it requires proper technique and high levels of strength and power.

title: Posterior Step to Overhead Reach
desc: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. Take a large step backward with one foot and lower your body until your back knee almost touches the ground. Push through your heel to return to standing, then repeat on the other side. Next, reach overhead with both arms, lifting your body off the ground as high as you can.

title: Push and Pull Bodyweight
desc: This workout consists of a series of bodyweight exercises that target the muscles of the upper body. The exercises are divided into push and pull movements, with each movement consisting of 3 sets of 8-12 reps. The workout is designed to improve strength, endurance, and flexibility in the upper body.

title: Medicine Ball Single Leg Deadlift
desc: This exercise should be done for 10-15 reps in each set, with 3 sets total. As an intermediate workout, this is a good challenge for your balance and stability.

title: Single Leg Foot Touch
desc: Stand on one leg and lift the other foot off the ground, keeping it straight and touching it to the knee of the standing leg.

title: Hanging Leg Hip Raise
desc: Perform leg raises while suspended in a hanging position. Engage your core and glutes to help lift your legs up towards the ceiling.

title: One Arm Towel Row
desc: Perform a rowing motion with one arm while holding onto a towel. Targets the upper body and core.

title: Side Plank Hip Adduction
desc: Perform side planks for 30 seconds, then alternate legs and perform hip adductions for 30 seconds. Repeat for 3 sets.

title: Lying Single Straight Leg Hip Extension
desc: Perform lying single straight leg hip extension exercises with dumbbells or resistance bands for glutes and legs. Female, Beginner level.

title: Reverse Chest Stretch
desc: This exercise targets the chest muscles through a series of stretches and movements. It is important to maintain proper form throughout the exercise to avoid injury.

title: Assisted Pulling Arms in Prone Position Chest Stretch
desc: This exercise should be done for 10-15 reps or 3-4 sets, with a time range of 5-20 minutes. It is suitable for beginners who want to improve their shoulder flexibility and range of motion.

title: Trap and Neck Stretch
desc: Stretches the trapezius muscle (trap) and neck muscles. Helps relieve tension and improve posture.

title: Reach up back stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips. Slowly reach your arms up towards the ceiling, stretching your back muscles.

title: Lying whole body stretch
desc: Stretch your entire body on your back while lying down. Move your arms and legs to different angles and hold each position for 10-15 seconds.

title: Sitting Lower Trunk Extensor Stretch
desc: Slowly lower your torso down towards your thighs, keeping your arms straight and palms facing down. Repeat for 5-10 minutes.

title: Seated Lower Trunk Extensor Lateral Flexor Stretch
desc: This stretch targets the lateral flexors and lower trunk muscles in a seated position. It helps to improve flexibility, balance, and posture.

title: Elbow Flexor Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and bend your left arm to stretch the muscles on the left side of your elbow. Hold for 30 seconds and then repeat with the right arm. Do 3 sets.

title: Forearm Pronator Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold onto a stable object for balance. Keeping your upper arms still, bend your elbows to 90 degrees and then fully stretch your pronator muscles by rotating your forearms inward and outward. Repeat for 3 sets of 15 reps.

title: Wrist Ulnar Deviator And Extensor Stretch
desc: Stretch the wrist and forearm muscles for 5-10 minutes, with a focus on the ulnar deviator and extensor muscles. This exercise is great for improving flexibility and reducing pain in the wrist and forearm area, especially for female individuals who are prone to wrist injuries.

title: Wrist Radial Deviator And Extensor Stretch
desc: Stretches the wrist radial deviator and extensor muscles. For 5-10 minutes, extend your hand with your palm facing downwards and rotate it in a circular motion with your fingers interlaced. Repeat this movement for 3 sets, each set consisting of 10-15 repetitions.

title: Wrist Radial Deviator And Flexor Stretch
desc: Stretch your wrist radial deviators and flexors for 5-10 reps in 2 sets to improve flexibility and reduce risk of injury.

title: Wrist Ulnar Deviator And Flexor Stretch
desc: Perform wrist circles in both clockwise and counterclockwise directions for 5-10 repetitions, 3 sets. This exercise helps to stretch the wrist ulnar deviator and flexor muscles, improving range of motion and preventing injuries.

title: Finger Extensor Stretch
desc: Perform finger stretches for 3 sets of 10 reps on each hand. Rest for 30 seconds between sets.

title: Diagonal Flexion Neck Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, then bend to the right and left, stretching your neck in a diagonal line.

title: Neck Protraction Stretch
desc: Slowly protrude your neck forward and hold for 10-15 seconds. Repeat 5-7 times.

title: Forward Flexion Neck Stretch
desc: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and slowly bend forward at the hips, stretching your neck and shoulders. Hold each stretch for 30 seconds and repeat for 5-10 minutes.

title: Neck Extensor And Rotational Stretch
desc: This beginner level neck extensor and rotational stretch exercise should be done for 5-10 reps, 3 sets. It targets the neck muscles, improving flexibility and range of motion.

title: Neck Flexor Stretch
desc: This exercise helps to stretch and relax the muscles in the neck. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and slowly tilt your head to the side, bringing your ear towards your shoulder. Hold for 30 seconds and then switch sides.

title: Lying Neck Extension Stretch
desc: Stretches the neck muscles by lying on your back and tilting your head to one side and then the other.

title: Extension And Inclination Neck Stretch
desc: This exercise stretches the muscles in the neck and improves flexibility. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and slowly tilt your head to the side, bringing your ear towards your shoulder. Hold for 30 seconds and then switch sides.

title: Calves Stretch Static Position
desc: Statically hold your calf muscles in a stretched position for 30 seconds on each leg.

title: Wrist Extensor Stretch
desc: Stretch your wrists by flexing and extending your fingers. Repeat for 3 sets of 10 reps each.

title: Wrist Flexor Stretch
desc: This stretch targets the wrist flexors, which can become tight and lead to discomfort and poor posture. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold your arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height.

title: Incline Push Press
desc: Perform incline push presses on a bench with dumbbells or barbell. Lie on an incline bench and press the weight upwards, keeping your core engaged throughout.

title: Hyperextension (VERSION 2)
desc: Targets the hamstrings, glutes and lower back muscles. The version 2 of this exercise is a bit more challenging than the original one.

title: Standing Leg Cross Abductor Stretch
desc: Perform leg abduction stretches while standing on one leg. Hold each stretch for 30 seconds and repeat for 3 sets.

title: Standing Leg Under Abductor Stretch
desc: Perform a standing leg lift while keeping the legs straight and lifting them under the hips. Repeat for 3 sets of 10-15 repetitions.

title: Single Heel Drop Achilles Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing straight ahead. Slowly lower one heel towards the ground, keeping your knee straight, then lift it back up to the starting position.

title: Crouching Heel Back Achilles Stretch
desc: Stretch your back, heels and Achilles tendon while crouching.

title: Kneeling Heel Down Achilles Stretch
desc: Stand on one leg, keeping the other foot on the ground with your heel pointing down. Slowly lower your body down towards the ground by bending your knee, keeping your back straight and core engaged.

title: Seated Knee Flexor And Hip Adductor Stretch
desc: Perform seated knee flexion and hip adduction stretches for 5-10 minutes, aiming to hold each stretch for 20-30 seconds and repeating 3-4 times per set.

title: Single Heel Drop Calf Stretch
desc: Perform a single heel drop calf stretch by standing on one leg and lowering the other heel to the ground. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat on the other side.

title: Tibial Flexion Stretch On Wall Bar
desc: Perform a wall-based tibial flexion stretch while standing with feet shoulder-width apart. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat for 3 sets.

title: Crouching Heel Back Calf Stretch
desc: This exercise is great for stretching the calves and back muscles. Crouch down on your heels and lean back, keeping your knees straight. Repeat for 5-10 reps, 3 times.

title: Seated Knee Up Extended Rotation Stretch
desc: Perform seated knee up extended rotation stretch for 3 sets of 10-15 reps each, resting for 30-60 seconds between sets. Aim to keep your back straight and engage your core throughout the exercise.

title: Lying Cross Over Knee Pull Down Stretch
desc: Stretches the hamstrings and lower back by hanging from a pull-up bar while kneeling on ones feet.

title: Hip External Rotator Stretch
desc: This stretch targets the hip muscles and can be done standing or sitting. Lean to one side and lift one leg, keeping it straight. Hold for 30 seconds and switch sides.

title: Lying Leg Tuck Hip Stretch
desc: Perform hip flexion and leg extension exercises while lying on your back. This exercise helps to stretch the hips and improve flexibility in the legs, which can be beneficial for runners and athletes who are looking to reduce their risk of injury.

title: Standing Outer Hip Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips. Slowly lift one leg out to the side, keeping it straight, then lower it back down. Repeat on the other side.

title: Sitting Rotational Hip Stretch
desc: Sit on the floor with your legs bent and feet flat. Slowly rotate your hips in a circular motion, first clockwise and then counterclockwise. Repeat for 30 seconds and rest for 30 seconds before repeating.

title: Standing Hip Flexor Stretch
desc: Perform a standing hip flexor stretch by standing with feet shoulder-width apart and bending forward at the hips to stretch the front of the hip. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat for 2-3 sets.

title: Flexion And Extension Hip Stretch
desc: Stretch the hip flexor muscles for 5-10 minutes, focusing on slow and controlled movements to improve range of motion in the hips.

title: Standing Shin Stretch
desc: Perform 3 sets of 15-second stretches on each leg, keeping your feet hip-width apart and knees slightly bent.

title: Seated Toe Extensor And Foot Everter Stretch
desc: This stretch targets the toe extensor muscles and foot everter muscles. It is a great way to improve flexibility in the feet and ankles.

title: Reverse Shoulder Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and slowly lift one arm overhead, keeping the elbow straight. Hold for 15-30 seconds and then switch sides.

title: One Arm Shoulder Flexor Stretch
desc: This stretch targets the shoulder flexors in one arm at a time, improving range of motion and reducing muscle imbalances. Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold onto a stable object for balance. Hold each stretch for 30 seconds to 1 minute.

title: Shoulder Extensor Adductor And Retractor Stretch
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10-15 repetitions of the stretch, holding each stretch for 20-30 seconds.

title: Shoulder Adductor Elevator And Protractor Stretch
desc: Perform shoulder elevation and protractor stretches for 5 minutes, 3-5 times a day. Females.

title: Bent Arm Shoulder Stretch
desc: Stretches the shoulders and upper body by holding bent arm overhead for 30 seconds each side.

title: Rotation Shoulder Stretch
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10-12 rotations with both arms, keeping the elbows bent at a 90-degree angle.

title: Rotator Cuff Stretch
desc: Perform the stretch 3 sets of 10 reps, holding each rep for 20-30 seconds. Rest for 30 seconds between sets.

title: Elbow Out Rotator Stretch
desc: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and hold onto a stable object for balance. Slowly move your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, then rotate your palms upwards. Repeat 10 times.

title: Arm Up Rotator Stretch
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a light dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. Keeping your upper arms still, lift the dumbbells upwards towards the ceiling until they are at shoulder height. Hold for 10-15 seconds and then lower back down to the starting position.

title: Kneeling One Arm Cross Body Stretch

title: External Shoulder Rotation Stretch

title: Hip Thrusts

title: Palms Out Forearm Stretch

title: Fingers Down Forearm Stretch

title: Wall Flexors Stretch

title: Thumb Stretch

title: Finger Extension Stretch

title: Cat Stretch (Version 2)

title: Cow Stretch

title: Split Jump to Box
desc: Perform a split jump and land on a box. For beginners, start with 5 reps and 3 sets, gradually increase as strength and endurance improve.

title: Seated Flexion And Extension Neck (male)
desc: This exercise strengthens the neck muscles through flexion and extension movements while seated. Do 5-10 reps of each movement for 3 sets.

title: Dip on Floor with Chair
desc: Perform dips on the floor using a chair for support. Start by placing the chair behind you and your feet on the ground, then lower your body down until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle.

title: Burpee with Push-up (female)
desc: Perform 5-10 burpees followed by 5-10 push-ups, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 3-4 sets.

title: Side Split
desc: Perform 3 sets of 12-15 reps on each side of the legs, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets. Focus on proper form and engaging the glutes and hamstrings to target the sides of the legs.

title: Warming-up in Lunge (one)
desc: Perform 1-2 sets of 8-12 lunges per leg, with a focus on proper form and control. Take a minute rest between sets.

title: Warming-up in Lunge (two)
desc: Perform lunges at a moderate pace for 2 sets of 10 reps, rest for 30 seconds between sets.

title: Warming-up in Lunge (three)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 lunges each leg with a weight that allows you to maintain proper form throughout the movement. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Warming-up in Lunge (five)
desc: Perform 5 lunges on each leg, taking a brief rest between sets.

title: Warming-up in Lunge (six)
desc: Perform 6 lunges on each leg, alternating legs with each rep

title: Warming-up in Lunge (seven)
desc: Perform 7 lunges on each leg, alternating legs with each rep.

title: Front Hamstring Stretch
desc: Stretches the front hamstrings by bending forward at the hips and reaching for the toes.

title: Downward Facing Dog
bodyPart: Back, Chest, Hips, Shoulders, Thighs, Upper Arms
desc: This exercise strengthens the arms, shoulders, and core while stretching the hamstrings and calves. It is a beginner-friendly pose that can be held for 5-10 minutes to improve flexibility and balance.

title: Warrior Pose (male)
desc: Hold this pose for 30 seconds, bend your right knee and stretch your arms overhead

title: Lying Leg Tuck Hip Stretch (male)
desc: This exercise targets the hip flexors and lower back muscles. Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Slowly lift your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them straight. Lower back down slowly and repeat for 10-15 reps.

title: Standing Balance Outer Hip Stretch
desc: This stretch targets the outer hips and helps improve balance. Stand with your feet hip-width apart and slowly lean to one side, holding for 30 seconds on each side.

title: Lying Leg Tuck Hip Stretch wth Overhead Hands (male)
desc: Perform a hip stretch while lying on your back. Keeping your legs straight, lift your legs up towards the ceiling and tuck them under for 10 reps. Hold for 30 seconds. Rest for 60 seconds and repeat 3 times.

title: Lying Leg Tuck Hip Back Stretch (male)
desc: This exercise should be done for 5-10 minutes, 3 sets of 10 reps each.

title: Lying Leg Tuck Hip Twist Stretch (male)
desc: This exercise targets the hips and legs, helping to improve flexibility and mobility. Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Tuck your knees into your chest and twist your legs from side to side, keeping your feet in contact with the floor.

title: Lying Leg Tuck Hip Back to Right Stretch (male)
desc: This exercise targets the lower back muscles and can help improve flexibility in the hips. Lie on your right side with your legs straight, then lift your top leg and tuck it towards your chest, keeping your feet together.

title: Lying Leg Tuck Hip Twist to Left Stretch (male)
desc: This exercise targets the lower abs and hips. Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Tuck your legs and lift them up towards the ceiling, then twist your hips to the left and hold for 30 seconds.

title: Alternate Sprinter Lunge
desc: Perform alternate sprinter lunges for 30 seconds, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 12 rounds.

duration.desc: 12 sets of 30 seconds of alternating sprinter lunges with rest in between each round

title: Split Sprinter High Lunge
desc: This workout involves performing high lunges while keeping your legs in a split position. It targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and core muscles. As an expert, you should perform 10-15 reps of this exercise for 3 sets.

title: Around the World Superman Hold
desc: Hold a superman position while moving your arms and legs in a circular motion around your body.

title: Inverted Row with Bent Knee between Chairs
desc: Perform inverted rows on a pull-up bar, keeping your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. Rest between each rep by stepping back onto the ground.

title: Inverted Chin Curl with Bent Knee between Chairs
desc: Perform inverted chin curls while keeping your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Rest between sets on a chair.

title: Single Leg Heel Touch Squat
desc: Perform single leg heel touch squats for 30 seconds, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 10 rounds.

title: Lying Straight Leg Marches
desc: Perform lying straight leg marches on a mat or bench. Lift your legs off the ground and march in place for 30 seconds, rest for 30 seconds, repeat for 12 reps.

title: Sliding Floor Bridge Curl on Towel
desc: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Slowly lift hips off the floor using a towel for support, keeping lower back pressed into the ground. Lower back down without touching the floor.

title: Self Assisted Inverted Pullover
desc: Perform inverted pull-ups with assist from a partner or resistance band. For beginner, perform 3-5 sets of 3-5 reps, for intermediate perform 4-6 sets of 5-8 reps and for expert perform 5-7 sets of 7-10 reps.

title: Full Squat Mobility
desc: Focus on proper technique and movement through a full range of motion. Aim to do 3 sets of 8-12 reps, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Front Plank with Leg Lift (male)
desc: Hold a front plank position for 30-60 seconds, lift one leg off the ground and hold for an additional 15-30 seconds, then lower it back down and repeat on the other side.

title: Elbow to Knee Side Plank Crunch (male)
desc: This exercise works your core muscles and legs by raising your knees and crunching your elbows while in a side plank position. Beginners can do 5-10 reps or 2-3 sets, and gradually increase the number of reps as they progress.

title: Camel Pose
desc: Stand on your feet with your knees slightly bent and your hands on your hips. Arch your back and lift your chest, looking up towards the ceiling.

title: Bodyweight Row in Doorway
desc: Perform a rowing motion with your body weight using the door frame as resistance. Keep your back straight and engage your core.

title: Seated In Out Leg Raise on Floor
desc: Perform leg raises on the floor while seated on a chair or bench. Keep your legs straight and lower them in a controlled manner.

title: Crunchy Frog on Floor
desc: Perform crunches while sitting on the floor with your legs bent and hands behind your head. Do 20-30 reps in a row, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 5-10 minutes.

title: Single Leg Sliding Floor Bridge Curl on Towel
desc: Lie on your back with both legs bent and feet flat on the floor. Slowly lift one leg up towards the ceiling while keeping the other leg in contact with the floor. Return to starting position and repeat for 3 sets of 12-15 reps.

title: Downward Facing Dog Toe Touch
desc: This workout targets the hamstrings, glutes, and calves by performing toe touches while in a downward facing dog position. Hold each rep for 2-3 seconds and rest for 1-2 minutes between sets.

title: Downward Facing Dog Spine Mobility
desc: This workout aims to improve spinal flexibility and range of motion through downward facing dog pose. It is ideal for beginners and intermediate level yogis looking to enhance their practice.

title: Alternate Punching
desc: Perform alternating punches with each arm, focusing on proper form and technique. Increase speed and power as you get stronger.

title: Boxer Shuffle
desc: This workout should be done for 5-10 minutes, with a focus on quick jabs and hooks followed by shuffling to evade an imaginary opponent. As a beginner, start with shorter sessions and gradually increase the duration as you build endurance.

title: Bulgarian Split Squat
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10-12 reps of Bulgarian split squats on each leg. Focus on keeping the back straight and the core engaged throughout the movement.

title: Elevanted Inverted Row between 3 Chairs
desc: Perform an elevated inverted row exercise using a barbell between 3 chairs. Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the movement. Aim to complete 3 sets of 8-12 reps.

title: Elevanted Inverted Underhand Grip Row between 3 Chairs
desc: Perform an underhand grip row between three chairs with your feet elevated. This exercise targets the latissimus dorsi, biceps, and core muscles.

title: Bodyweight Drop Jump Squat
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps of the Bodyweight Drop Jump Squat exercise, as described. Target a range of 5-8 reps and sets for beginners.

title: Side Shuttle
desc: Perform side-to-side shuttles by alternating between a high knee lift and a wide stance for 5-10 minutes.

title: Quick Feet (VERSION 2)
desc: Perform quick footwork drills to improve your agility and speed. Include movements such as carioca, ladder drills, and cone drills.

title: Power Push Aways
desc: Perform 3 sets of 8-12 reps of each exercise, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets. Complete 3-4 exercises for a total of 15-20 minutes.

title: High Knee Run
desc: Run on a treadmill or track while lifting one knee towards the chest and flexing the opposite leg. Perform for 30 seconds, then switch legs.

title: Superman Row with Towel
desc: Perform a rowing motion with towel held in front of chest, keeping back straight and legs straight. This exercise targets the muscles of the upper body, including the chest, shoulders, and back.

title: Seated Shoulder Flexor Depresor Retractor Stretch Bent Knee
desc: This workout involves stretching and flexibility exercises targeting the shoulder muscles, as well as retractors and bent knee stretches to improve overall range of motion. It is an excellent exercise for beginners looking to improve their posture and reduce tension in the shoulders.

title: Bridge Pose Yoga Stretch
desc: This yoga stretch targets the lower back, glutes and hamstrings. It helps to improve flexibility, balance and posture.

title: Side Bridge with Arm Leg Swing
desc: Lie on your side and lift legs and arms off the ground, alternating sides.

title: Single Leg Deadlift with Knee Lift
desc: Perform 5-10 repetitions of the Single Leg Deadlift with Knee Lift exercise, resting for 30 seconds between sets. As you get stronger, increase the number of repetitions or the duration of each set.

title: Scissors (advanced) (male)
desc: This advanced workout targets the core muscles of the body, including the obliques and lower back. It involves a series of rapid movements with the legs and arms, requiring proper form and control to execute safely.

title: Alternate Lying Floor Leg Raise (male)
desc: Perform leg raises on a floor by alternating legs in a slow and controlled manner.

title: Chest Dip (female)
desc: Perform chest dips by hanging from a bar with your hands shoulder-width apart. Lower your body until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle, then lift back up to the starting position.

title: Hanging Straight Leg Hip Raise (female)
desc: Perform hip raises by suspending yourself from a pull-up bar with straight legs. Engage your core and lift your hips up towards the ceiling, then lower back down.

title: Standing Hamstrings and Back Stretch
desc: Perform 3 sets of 12-15 reps of standing hamstring and back stretches. Rest for 30-60 seconds between sets.

title: Sitting Sumo Mobility Stretch
desc: This workout focuses on mobility and stretching of the hips, legs, and back while sitting in a sumo position. It can help improve flexibility and range of motion, reduce stiffness, and prevent injuries.

title: Sitting Sumo Right Twist Stretch
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps sitting in a sumo position and twisting to the right, resting for 30 seconds between sets.

title: Sitting Sumo Left Twist Stretch
desc: Sit on the floor with your legs crossed and feet touching. Twist your torso to the left, keeping your feet and hips facing forward. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat on the other side.

title: Sitting Sumo with Arms-Up Mobility Stretch
desc: This stretch is great for mobilizing the shoulders and torso while seated. It can be done in a sumo position to help open up the chest and improve posture.

title: Wheel Run
desc: This beginner-level workout involves running on a wheel for 5-10 minutes. it's important to start slow and gradually increase speed and duration as you become more comfortable with the movement.

title: Jump Box (male)
desc: Perform box jumps on a 24-inch or higher step for 3 sets of 12 reps, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Short Stride Run
desc: Perform a 30 second run at maximum effort followed by a 30 second walk. Repeat for 15 minutes.

title: Reverse Plank with Leg Lift
desc: Perform a reverse plank position while lifting one leg, holding for 20-30 seconds and repeating on the other side.

title: Power Point Plank
desc: Hold a plank position for 30 seconds. Rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 3-5 sets.

title: Standing Archer
desc: Perform standing archery with a bow and arrows. Hold the bow vertically in front of you and shoot arrows at a target. Aim for accuracy and control, focus on proper form and technique.

title: Ski Step
desc: Perform ski steps on a step bench alternating legs with each rep for 5-10 minutes

title: Back And Forth Step
desc: Perform step-ups on a bench or platform, alternating legs with each rep.

title: Shoulder Tap
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands at your sides. Tap your shoulders with your right hand, then left. Repeat for 10 reps.

title: High Knee Sprints
desc: This exercise is best suited for experienced athletes who are looking to improve their speed and endurance. The high knee movement helps to engage the quadriceps muscles, while the sprinting increases the heart rate and burns calories.

title: Forward Pulse Lunge with Hands Overhead
desc: Step forward with one foot and slowly lower your body until your back knee almost touches the ground. Keeping your front shin vertical, push back up to the starting position and repeat with the other leg.

title: Double Jump Squat
desc: Perform double jump squats for 3 sets of 10 reps each, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Cardio Lunge
desc: Perform lunges while holding dumbbells or a resistance band for 3 sets of 12 reps each. Rest for 60 seconds between sets.

title: Single Leg Step Up (female)
desc: Step up on one leg, then the other, alternating legs

title: Standing Single Leg Calf Raise with Support (female)
desc: This exercise targets the calf muscles in the standing position with support. it's a great beginner-level exercise for developing strength and stability in the lower legs.

title: Split Squat with Roll
desc: Perform 3 sets of 12-15 reps, rest for 30-60 seconds between sets.

title: Split Lateral Squat with Roll
desc: Perform split squats with lateral movements to target the legs and glutes. Include a rollout at the top of each rep.

title: Lateral Raise with Towel
desc: Perform lateral raises with a towel under your feet for an added challenge. Focus on proper form and control throughout the movement. Aim to complete 5-10 reps in each set.

title: Bulgarian Split Squat with Chair
desc: Perform split squats on a chair for 3 sets of 10-12 reps, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets. Focus on keeping your back straight and your knees in line with your toes.

title: Assisted Pistol Squat with Bed Sheet
desc: Perform a pistol squat while holding onto a bed sheet for balance and support. Start with 3 sets of 10 reps and gradually increase the number of reps as you progress.

title: Biceps Curl with Bed Sheet
desc: Perform biceps curls using a bed sheet as resistance. Male, Beginner level.

title: Inverted Row with Bed Sheet
desc: Perform inverted rows on a bed sheet using your own body weight as resistance. Start by lying face up on the bed sheet with your feet firmly planted on the floor and your hands gripping the edge of the sheet for support. Slowly lift your shoulders off the sheet, keeping your lower back pressed into the ground, and hold for a 2-3 second count. Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Reverse Push-up
desc: Perform reverse push-ups for 5-10 minutes, resting for 30 seconds between sets. For beginners, start with 3 sets of 5-7 reps and gradually increase the number of sets and reps as you become more comfortable with the movement.

title: Curtsey Squat
desc: Targets the glutes and legs with a challenging movement that requires proper form.

title: Alternate Punching (female)
desc: Perform punches with alternate hands (left, right, left, right) for 5-10 minutes. Rest for 30 seconds between sets.

title: Bodyweight Pulse Squat (female)
desc: Perform squats while pulsing your bodyweight up and down, aiming to complete 10-15 reps in each set.

title: Lunge with Leg Lift (female)
desc: Perform lunges for 30 seconds, then lift the knee to chest and hold for 10 seconds. Repeat on other leg.

title: Elevanted Push-Up
desc: Perform push-ups on your knees with a dumbbell or medicine ball for added resistance. Aim to complete 10-15 reps in each set and perform 3 sets total.

title: Pulse Row (male)
desc: This intermediate workout requires you to use a rowing machine for 3 sets of 10 reps, with a 1 minute rest in between each set. You will be targeting your legs, glutes, and cardio, so be prepared to feel the burn!!

title: Decline Shoulder Tap
desc: Tap your shoulders in a decline position

title: Pseudo Planche Push-up
desc: Perform push-ups while keeping your legs straight and elevating your hips on a bench or chair. Aim for 3 sets of 12 reps.

title: Mid Air Lateral Raises With Switching Palms
desc: Perform lateral raises with alternating palms in mid air. For beginners, start with 5-10 reps per set and 3 sets. Gradually increase the number of reps as you progress.

title: Lying Floor Hyperextension
desc: Perform lying floor hyperextensions for 10-15 reps, 3 times. Male

title: Lying Double Legs Hammer Curl with Towel
desc: This exercise works multiple muscle groups in the arms and legs. It targets the biceps, hamstrings, and glutes.

title: Lying Single Legs Reverse Biceps Curl with Towel
desc: Perform lying single leg reverse biceps curls with a towel for added resistance.

duration.desc: 3 sets of 12-15 reps with a hold time of 20-30 seconds

title: Handboard Slope Hang
desc: Perform a handboard slope hang for 30 seconds, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 5 sets.

title: Handboard Open Hand Grip
desc: Perform a handboard open hand grip exercise for 3 sets of 10 reps, with a time range of 5-10 minutes.

title: Handboard Half Crimp
desc: Perform half crimp on a handboard with your hands facing away from you. Hold for 2 seconds and then release.

title: Handboard Hang with 90 Degree Elbow
desc: Hold the hang for 30-60 seconds, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 3-5 sets.

title: Handboard Hang with 135 Degree Elbow
desc: Perform a hang from a pull-up bar with your elbows at a 135 degree angle for 8-10 reps in 2 sets. This exercise targets the upper back muscles and is great for beginners to build strength and endurance.

title: Bulgarian Jump Squat
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps of Bulgarian jump squats. Start with a barbell and lower the weight as you get stronger.

title: Duck Walk (male)
desc: Step forward with one foot and transfer the weight to that foot. Quickly bring the other foot to meet the first foot, stepping through the space in a duck-like motion. Repeat for 30 seconds, then rest for 30 seconds before repeating for 2-3 sets.

title: Frog Reverse Hyperextension (on a bench) (male)
desc: Lie on a flat back bench with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Slowly lift hips up towards ceiling, squeezing glutes at top of movement. Lower hips back down to starting position.

title: Jump Box Over (male)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 jump box overs, resting for 30 seconds between sets.

duration.desc: 3 sets of 10 reps in a range of 10-15 minutes

title: Pike Press (between benches)
desc: Perform pike presses on a set of parallel bars, using a weight that allows you to complete the given number of repetitions with proper form.

title: Bodyweight Kneeling Push-up Row
desc: Perform kneeling push-ups with a row motion using your feet, keeping your back straight and engaging your core.

title: Decline Pike Press (between benches)
desc: Perform decline pike presses between two benches. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. Push back up to the starting position.

title: Handstand Shoulder Press with Wall (between benches)
desc: Perform handstand shoulder presses against a wall between two benches. This exercise works the shoulders, chest, and triceps.

title: Bodyweight Single Leg Deadlift
desc: Perform a single leg deadlift using only your bodyweight. Stand on one leg and hold the other foot with your hand, keeping your back straight and core engaged.

title: Circles Knee Stretch (female)
desc: Perform circles with your knees while standing or sitting. Move your knees in a circular motion, first clockwise and then counterclockwise. Repeat for 30 seconds to 1 minute on each set.

title: Decline Push-up (Kneeling) (female)
desc: Perform push-ups on your knees instead of your toes. This modification targets the muscles in your upper chest and shoulders more.

title: Romanian Chair Sit-Up (VERSION 2)
desc: Perform sit-ups on a Romanian chair for an explosive core workout.

title: Air Squat (female)
desc: Perform air squats with proper form and technique, focusing on keeping the back straight, engaging the core, and landing softly on the heels.

title: Crawl to Crab (female)
desc: A beginner level workout that targets the legs and core. In this exercise you will start in a high plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart, then lower yourself down into a crawling position while keeping your core engaged. From there, you will bring one knee towards the other, mimicking the movement of a crab. Repeat on the other side and continue alternating for 30 seconds or more.

title: High Knees Lunge (female)
desc: Step forward with one foot and lower your body until your back knee almost touches the ground. Push back up to standing and repeat with the other leg.

title: Spider Plank (female)
desc: Hold a plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core muscles to support your body and maintain the position for 30 seconds.

title: Front to Side Plank (female)
desc: Hold a side plank for 30-60 seconds on each side, rest for 15-30 seconds between sides.

title: Twist Step Stretch (female)
desc: This workout involves a series of twists and steps while standing, followed by stretches to improve flexibility. It is recommended to do this exercise for 5-10 minutes.

title: High Knee Squat (VERSION 2) (female)
desc: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, then bend your knees and lift your body off the ground, keeping your back straight. Lower your body down into a squat position, then push back up to the starting position.

title: Side Step Front Plank (female)
desc: Perform side step front planks for 5-10 reps, resting for 30 seconds between sets. Aim to complete 2 sets of 5-10 reps.

title: Forward Step Front Plank (female)
desc: Hold a front plank position for 30 seconds while stepping forward with one foot. Then, step backward with the opposite foot and repeat on the other side.

title: Forward to Side to Rear Lunge (female)
desc: Perform lunges in a forward direction, then switch legs and lunge to the side, then switch legs again and perform rears lunges for 10-15 minutes

title: Seated Flutter Kick
desc: Perform seated flutter kicks with a dumbbell in each hand. Quickly alternate legs and keep your core engaged.

title: Push-up Hand by Hand
desc: Perform push-ups with hands touching each other. Aim for 5-10 reps in 3 sets.

title: Long Arm Crunch
desc: Lie on your back with hands behind head and lift shoulders off floor, holding for 1-2 seconds before releasing. (5-10 minutes)

title: Wide Hand Push-up (female)
desc: Perform push-ups with hands shoulder-width apart. Do 12 reps.

title: Inverted Shrug (on parallel bars)
desc: Perform inverted shrugs on parallel bars, using your own body weight as resistance. Hold each rep for a moment of emphasis and complete 10-15 reps in 3 sets.

title: Single Leg Glute Bridge with Knee to Chest
desc: This exercise targets the glutes and core muscles. As a beginner, you should focus on proper form and control throughout the movement. Start with 10-15 reps in 3 sets, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Side Lying Leg Raise
desc: Perform leg raises on your side while lying down. This exercise targets the lower abs and obliques.

title: Reverse Crunch to Dead Bug (male)
desc: This exercise combines a reverse crunch with a dead bug movement. Start in a plank position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your feet hip-width apart. Engage your core and lift your shoulders off the ground, keeping your lower back pressed into the ground. Hold for 2 seconds, then release back down to the starting position. Repeat for 3 sets of 10 reps.

title: Lying Leg Hip Side Raise on Floor
desc: Perform hip side raises while lying on your back with your legs straight and hips stacked. Lift your hips off the floor, squeezing your glutes at the top of each rep.

title: Squat Hold Calf Raise
desc: Perform a deep squat hold for 30 seconds, then immediately perform 10 calf raises. Repeat for 5 sets.

title: Trap Bar Jump Squat
desc: Perform trap bar jump squats for 3 sets of 8-10 reps, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Jump Pistol Squat Box (male)
desc: Perform jump squats while holding a box with both hands. Lower your body until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle, then explosively jump up and return to the starting position. Aim for 3 sets of 8-12 reps, with 1-2 minutes rest in between sets.

title: Jumping Pistol Squat
desc: Perform pistol squats while jumping up and landing softly on the balls of your feet. Repeat for 3 sets of 12 reps.

title: Fly agains Chains
desc: This workout involves using chains as resistance to fly through the air, increasing strength and endurance. Perform 3 sets of 10 reps each, with a rest time of 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Chin-Up Around the Bar
desc: Perform chin-ups around a bar with both hands. Aim to do 3 sets of 12 reps each.

title: Climbing Monkey Bars
desc: This workout involves climbing monkey bars with different grips and angles. You will need to use your arms, shoulders, back, and core muscles to complete the exercises. Start by hanging from the bar with both hands and then switch to a wide overhand grip, then a narrow underhand grip, and finally a neutral grip. After that, try different angles like 45 degrees and 90 degrees. Do 3 sets of 8-12 reps for each grip and angle.

title: Tiger Tail Forearm
desc: This workout involves swinging a weighted barbell in a circular motion to target your forearms. it's a great exercise for building grip strength and endurance.

title: Tiger Tail Neck
desc: This exercise targets the muscles in the upper back and shoulders, helping to improve posture and reduce tension. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent, then lift your arms up and down in a slow and controlled motion.

title: Assault Run
desc: Perform high-intensity interval training by running at maximum speed for 30 seconds followed by 30 seconds of rest. Repeat for 10-20 minutes.

title: Single Leg Board Jump
desc: Perform jumps on a single leg on a board, alternating legs with each jump. This exercise targets the legs and glutes, improving balance and strength.

title: Straight Leg Hip Bridge
desc: Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. Slowly lift your hips off the ground, squeezing your glutes at the top of the movement. Lower your hips back down to the starting position.

title: Stepdown Squat
desc: Perform stepdown squats for 3 sets of 10-12 reps. Start with a weight that allows you to complete the given number of reps with proper form.

title: Backwards Run
desc: Perform a run backwards from the starting point to the finishing line without looking back. Must be done at an intermediate level of fitness or higher.

title: Calf Stretch with Rope (female)
desc: Perform calf stretches with a rope to target the muscles in your lower legs. Stand on a step or platform and hold one end of a rope in each hand, keeping your arms straight. Slowly pull the rope towards your body, stretching your calf muscles. Repeat for 3 sets of 15 reps.

title: Intermediate Hip Flexor and Quad Stretch (female)
desc: Perform hip flexor and quad stretches for 30 seconds on each leg. Repeat for 3 sets.

title: Middle Back Stretch (male)
desc: Stretches the muscles in the upper and middle back, improving flexibility and reducing tension

title: Neck Side Stretch (female)
desc: Stretches the muscles on one side of the neck by tilting the head to the opposite side and holding for 30 seconds.

title: Rear Deltoid Stretch (female)
desc: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. Slowly reach behind you and clasp your hands together. Hold for 30 seconds, then release.

title: Reverse Dip (female)
desc: Perform reverse dips on a bench or chair with your hands facing away from you. Lower your body until your arms are bent at a 90-degree angle, then push back up to the starting position.

title: Runners Stretch (female)
desc: Perform each stretch for 20-30 seconds, repeat 2-3 times and move on to the next one. Start with the ones that feel tightest or most uncomfortable to you.

title: Seated Wide Angle Pose Sequence (female)
desc: This workout sequence targets the hips and legs. It includes a series of seated wide angle poses that will help to stretch and strengthen these areas.

title: Side Wrist Pull Stretch (female)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10-15 repetitions on each side of the wrist pull stretch, holding the stretch for 20-30 seconds. Rest for 30-60 seconds between sets.

duration.desc: 3 sets of 10-15 reps, holding for 20-30 seconds, resting for 30-60 seconds between sets, total duration: 10-15 minutes

title: Slopes Towards Stretch (male)
desc: This workout involves a series of exercises that target the muscles in the legs and glutes. It starts with a warm-up on the treadmill followed by a series of hill sprints, then moves to strength training exercises such as lunges, squats, and deadlifts. Finally, it ends with a stretching routine to help prevent soreness and improve flexibility.

title: Spine Stretch (female)
desc: This workout is designed to stretch and strengthen the muscles in your spine. It involves a series of gentle movements that can be done seated or standing, with a focus on proper posture and alignment. Beginners can do this exercise for 5-10 minutes per session, 3-4 times a week.

title: Standing Back Rotation Stretch (female)
desc: This stretch targets the muscles in your upper back, shoulders, and arms. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips.

title: Standing Gastrocnemius Calf Stretch (female)
desc: Perform a standing calf stretch by leaning forward and bending your knees. Keep your back straight and hold for 15-30 seconds.

title: Standing Lateral Stretch (female)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps each of standing lateral stretches. Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your hands on your hips. Slowly twist your torso to the left and right, keeping your arms straight.

title: Wrist Circles (female)
desc: Perform wrist circles by rotating your hands in a circular motion both clockwise and counterclockwise for 3 sets of 10-15 reps each

title: Reverse Crunch Kick
desc: Perform reverse crunches while holding a dumbbell in each hand. Then perform a kick with your legs while keeping the dumbbells close to your chest.

title: Bench Reverse Crunch Circle
desc: Perform bench reverse crunches while lying on a bench and holding a medicine ball. Complete 3 sets of 15 reps.

title: Side Plank Oblique Crunch
desc: Perform side plank for 30-60 seconds, then perform oblique crunches for another 30-60 seconds. Repeat for 3 sets.

title: Bodyweight Standing Military Press
desc: Perform standing military press with bodyweight using your arms and shoulders. Start in a standing position with feet shoulder-width apart, then push your body upwards using your arms and shoulders to elevate yourself.

title: Bench Dip on floor (VERSION 2)
desc: Perform dip exercises on a flat bench using your own body weight for resistance. Version 2 adds an extra challenge by requiring you to perform the dips from a lower starting position, which will increase the difficulty level and engage more muscle groups.

title: Counterbalanced Skater Squat (male)
desc: Perform counterbalanced skater squats for 3 sets of 10 reps, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets. This exercise targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and core muscles, and is appropriate for intermediate fitness level individuals.

title: Single Leg Dip on floor
desc: Perform dips on one leg while keeping the other foot on the ground, aim to complete 5-10 reps or 3 sets.

title: Animal Resting Yoga Pose
desc: This yoga pose involves lying on your back with your arms and legs relaxed. Take deep breaths and focus on the sensation of the pose. it's great for reducing stress and anxiety.

title: Bodyweight Standing Biceps Curl (VERSION 2)
desc: Perform standing bicep curls using your bodyweight. Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. Keeping your upper arms still, bend your elbows to curl the weight towards your shoulders.

title: Crocodile Yoga Pose
desc: Lie on your stomach with arms and legs extended, lift chest and head off the ground, hold for 30 seconds

title: Handstand Walk
desc: Perform handstand walks for 30 seconds, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 10 minutes

title: Body Saw Plank
desc: Hold a plank position for 30 seconds, rest for 1 minute and repeat for 3 sets.

title: Hip Roll Plank
desc: Perform a plank while rolling your hips in a large circle. Keep your core engaged and body in a straight line from head to heels.

title: Prayer Squat Yoga Pose
desc: This yoga pose targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and core muscles. It also helps to improve balance and flexibility.

title: Alternate Shoulder Flexion Back to Wall
desc: Perform shoulder flexions while keeping your back against a wall. Alternate shoulders with each rep.

title: Standing Seal Yoga Pose
desc: Stand with feet hip-width apart and arms extended overhead. Bend your knees slightly and round your back, lowering your chest to the ground while keeping your legs straight.

title: Straight Angle Yoga Pose
desc: Perform a straight angle pose with your body. Stand with your feet hip-width apart and arms at your sides. Keeping your spine long, bend your knees slightly and lower your body into a squat. From there, lift your hips up and back, keeping your arms straight and your core engaged.

title: Swaying Palm Tree Yoga Pose
desc: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and slowly sway your arms from side to side, as if you are a palm tree in the wind. This exercise will help improve your flexibility and balance.

title: The Eagle Yoga Pose
desc: Stretch your arms and legs, bend forward and balance on your hands and feet.

title: Tiger Yoga Pose
desc: This pose is great for stretching and flexibility, helps to improve balance and strength.

title: Warrior II Yoga Pose
desc: Perform Warrior II Yoga Pose for 5-10 minutes, maintaining proper form throughout. For beginners, start with a shorter time frame and gradually increase as you build strength and flexibility.

title: Sliding Leg Bird Dog
desc: This exercise works multiple muscle groups in the legs and core. It involves sliding your legs side to side while keeping your core engaged.

title: High Knee Squat (VERSION 2) (male)
desc: Perform high knee squats, focusing on proper form and technique. Increase the height of your knees as you get stronger.

title: Alternating Hamstring Curl with Punche
desc: Perform alternating hamstring curls while punching a heavy bag. Rest for 1 min and repeat for 3-4 sets.

title: Glute Ham Raise (VERSION 2)
desc: Targets glutes and hamstrings, improving strength and muscle growth. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, then bend your knees slightly and lower your body down into a squat position. From there, lift your hips up towards the ceiling, squeezing your glutes and pushing your heels towards the ground. Repeat for 10-12 reps.

title: Lying Ab Press (male)
desc: Perform lying abdominal crunches while holding a weight or resistance band. Male, Intermediate level.

title: Side Bridge with Bent Leg (female)
desc: Perform a side bridge exercise while keeping one leg bent and the other straight. Aim to hold for 2-3 seconds on each side, completing 3 sets of 10-15 reps on each side.

title: Bodyweight Full Squat with Overhead Press
desc: This exercise is best suited for advanced individuals who have a strong foundation in strength training. The overhead press adds an additional challenge to the squat, requiring stability and control throughout the movement. Start with 10-15 reps per set and perform 3 sets total.

title: Above Head Chest Stretch (female)
desc: Stretch your chest by raising your arms above your head and clasping your hands together. For beginners, perform 5-10 reps

title: Burpee Squat
desc: Perform burpees and squats for 30 seconds, alternating between the two movements.

title: Push Through Reach
desc: A full-body workout that targets the chest, shoulders, triceps, and core. Includes push-ups, reach-ups, and tricep dips.

title: Couch Stretch
desc: Perform stretching exercises for the upper body and legs on a couch. Male. Beginner.

title: Kneeling Lat Stretch on Bench
desc: Perform a kneeling lat stretch on a bench with your hands on the edge and your feet flat on the floor. Hold for 30 seconds or perform 5-10 reps.

title: Boxing Right Cross (with boxing bag)
desc: Perform a right cross punch with a boxing bag, focusing on proper form and technique. This exercise is best suited for those with prior experience in boxing or other similar martial arts.

title: Boxing Right Hook (with boxing bag)
desc: This workout involves throwing a right hook punch with a boxing bag. It targets the muscles in the upper body, particularly the shoulders and triceps.

title: Front Snap Kick Kickboxing (with boxing bag)
desc: Perform rapid-fire front kicks with a snapping motion, targeting a heavy bag or pad. Increases speed, power and agility in the legs.

title: Hook Kick Kickboxing (with boxing bag)
desc: This high-energy workout combines martial arts techniques with aerobic exercise for a full-body fitness experience. You'll learn kicks, punches, and defensive moves while burning calories and building strength.

title: Boxing Jab (with partner)
desc: Perform jabs with a boxing partner. Stand facing your partner with your feet shoulder-width apart, and your hands in a neutral position.

title: Boxing Left Uppercut (with partner)
desc: Perform a left uppercut punch with your partner standing in front of you, using proper form and technique. For Expert level, perform 10-20 reps or 3-5 sets.

title: Boxing Right Cross (with partner)
desc: Perform a right cross punch with your partner standing across from you for 5-10 minutes as an Expert.

title: Boxing Right Uppercut (with partner)
desc: Perform a right uppercut punch with a partner, alternating between partners and focusing on proper technique.

title: Front Knee Kick Kickboxing (with partner)
desc: This kickboxing workout focuses on the front knee kick, a powerful technique that targets the core and legs. it's performed with a partner, allowing for added resistance and challenge. Each round consists of 30 seconds of front knee kicks followed by 30 seconds of rest. Repeat for 10-15 minutes or until you feel fatigued.

title: Front Snap Kick Kickboxing (with partner)
desc: This kickboxing exercise works the legs, glutes and core. Partner required for the exercise.

title: PVC External Rotation
desc: This exercise strengthens the muscles of the upper arm and shoulder. Hold a PVC pipe at shoulder height with both hands, then rotate your arms in an external rotation motion (away from your body).

title: PVC Front Rack Stretch
desc: Stretch your front rack muscles with this simple yet effective exercise. Stand over a pair of PVC pipes and grip them with an underhand grip, then lift your arms to shoulder height and hold for 10-15 seconds.

title: PVC Overhead Squat
desc: Perform overhead squats with a PVC pipe held at shoulder height. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and slowly lower the pipe down towards the ground while keeping your body in a straight line. Then, push the pipe back up to the starting position.

title: Bodyweight Standing Around World Wall Supported
desc: Perform a standing bodyweight workout while holding onto the wall for support. Work your way around the room using different grips and stances to challenge yourself.

title: Bodyweight Standing Military Press Wall Supported
desc: Perform bodyweight standing military press with wall support, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets. For a beginner, aim for 3 sets of 8-12 reps.
