title: Scorpion Stretch
desc: Perform a scorpion stretch on each leg by bending one knee and grabbing your ankle with the opposite hand. Hold for 30 seconds and switch legs.

title: Kneeling Shoulder Tap Push-up (female)
desc: Perform kneeling shoulder taps while holding a push-up position. Alternate arms each rep.

title: Arm Crossover (female)
desc: This exercise targets the triceps and shoulders. It involves crossing your arms over each other and then bringing them back to the starting position.

title: Overhead Clap (female)
desc: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold dumbbells or kettlebells at shoulder height. Squeeze your shoulder blades together and clap the weights overhead, then lower them back to the starting position.

title: Palm-up   Palm down Rotation (female)
desc: Perform palm-up and palm-down rotations with your arms while lying on your back. For a beginner, start with 5-10 reps or 3 sets.

title: Bodyweight Overhead Triceps Extension (female)
desc: Perform triceps extensions using your bodyweight. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand.

title: Seated Shoulder Flexor Depresor Retractor Stretch Bent Knee (female)
desc: This exercise should be done for 5-10 minutes, 3 sets of 10 reps.

title: Kneeling Leg Half Circle (male)
desc: Perform half circles with your legs while kneeling on one knee. Alternate legs with each rep.

title: Alternating Superman
desc: Lie on your stomach with your arms extended in front of you. Alternate bringing each arm forward and backward, keeping your legs straight for 3 sets of 12 reps.

title: Bar Biceps Curl
desc: Perform biceps curls using a barbell. Lie on your back and curl the bar towards your shoulders, then lower it back down to the starting position.

title: Bodyweight Standing Sissy Squat
desc: Perform standing sissy squats with bodyweight. Start in a standing position with feet shoulder-width apart, then lower your body down into a squat and back up to the starting position.

title: Glute Ham Single Leg Hyperextension
desc: This exercise targets the glutes and hamstrings, strengthening them to improve overall lower body function. It can also help to improve balance and stability.

title: Incline Alternate Flutter Kicks
desc: Perform alternating flutter kicks on an incline bench for 10-15 reps, resting 60-90 seconds between sets. For an intermediate level workout, aim to complete 3 sets of 10-15 reps.

title: Jump Split with Hands on Hip
desc: Perform a split jump while keeping your hands on your hips. Land softly on both feet and immediately jump up again, repeating the movement for 5-10 reps in 2 sets.

title: Supported Squat (female)
desc: Perform squats with a support under the chest or knees to work the legs and glutes. Complete 3 sets of 10 reps for each leg.

title: Triceps Press (high bar position)
desc: Perform triceps presses with a high bar position, using dumbbells or a barbell. Complete 3 sets of 10-12 reps.

title: Ring Elevated Row
desc: Perform dumbbell rows on a raised ring with feet elevated, using 10-15 reps per set for 3 sets.

title: Ring Reverse Ab Rollout
desc: Perform reverse crunches on a suspension ring while holding onto the rings for stability. This exercise targets the lower abs, obliques, and lower back.

title: Jump Skip Rope
desc: Jump and skip rope for 30 seconds, rest for 1 minute. Repeat for 15 minutes.

title: Sliding Floor Pulldown on Towel (VERSION 2)
desc: Targets the lats, traps and rhomboids. Perform pulldowns using a towel under your feet for added resistance.

title: Lying Rear Lateral Raise
desc: Perform lateral raises while lying on your back with your legs bent and feet flat on the ground. Hold a dumbbell in each hand and slowly raise the weights out to the sides until they are at shoulder height.

title: Depth Jump to Broad Jump
desc: This workout involves jumping from a depth of 10 inches to a broad jump of 20 inches. It requires good balance and coordination, and can be challenging for beginners.

title: Depth Jump
desc: Perform a series of depth jumps, landing softly on both feet. Aim for 3 sets of 10-15 reps.

title: Lateral Walk Push-up

title: Push-up to Side Plank (VERSION 2)
desc: Perform 3 rounds of 30 seconds each in a side plank position after a push-up. This exercise targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps.

title: Side Plank Leg Lift
desc: Perform a side plank for 30-60 seconds while alternately lifting one leg and lowering it back down to the starting position. Repeat on the other side.

title: Prayer Push (female)

title: Bridge Hip Abduction (male)
desc: Perform hip abductions on a bridge position. Hold each rep for 3-4 seconds before switching sides.

title: Side Lying Outward Knee Kick
desc: Perform side lying leg kicks while keeping your core engaged and lower body stable. Aim for 10-15 reps in each set, completing 2-3 sets total.

title: Glute Ham Raise with Extended Arms
desc: Perform glute ham raises on an incline bench while holding dumbbells in both hands. Keep your arms extended throughout the movement.

title: Hanging Half Windmill

title: Elevated Single Leg Squat
desc: Perform a single leg squat on an elevated surface (step, bench, etc.) maintaining proper form and balance. 3 sets of 8-12 reps on each leg.

title: Kneeling Half Triceps Extension
desc: Perform half triceps extensions on your knees with dumbbells. Hold for 10-15 seconds and repeat for 3 sets.

title: Inverted Wide to Narrow Row
desc: Perform inverted wide grip rows with a barbell or dumbbells, then transition to narrow grip rows. Focus on proper form and control throughout the movement.

title: Narrow Top Half Pull-up (female)
desc: Perform a pull-up movement with a narrow grip (hands shoulder-width apart) and focus on bringing the chest to the bar.

title: High Bar Inverted Row
desc: Perform inverted rows on a high bar with your feet resting on the ground. Hold onto the bar with an underhand grip and pull yourself up until your chest is above the bar.

title: Long Lever Lying Back Extension

title: Lying Air Cycles (female)
desc: Perform lying air cycles for 30 seconds, resting for 10 seconds between each cycle. Aim to complete 3-5 sets.

title: Reverse Plank (VERSION 2)

title: Lying Around the World (female)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps of the exercise, resting for 30 seconds between sets.

title: Chest Out Hands Behind (Hold) (female)
desc: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold hands behind your back at shoulder height, and press your chest forward.

title: Seated Sky Look
desc: Perform 3 sets of 8-12 reps of seated sky looks on a set of dumbbells. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Bodyweight Forward Lunge (Smaller Stance Upright Torso)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 12 reps for each leg, with a rest time of 30-60 seconds between sets. Focus on maintaining proper form and engaging your core throughout the exercise.

title: Jump Shrug
desc: Perform a set of 12-15 reps of jump squats, followed by 12-15 reps of shrugs. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Press Under
desc: Perform a set of 10-12 reps of press unders, rest for 60-90 seconds between sets. Aim to complete 3-4 sets.

title: Negative Dragon Flag
desc: Perform negative reps of dragon flags to failure. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Kneeling Modified Hindu Push-up (male)
desc: Perform modified push-ups on your knees instead of your toes. Start in a kneeling position with your hands shoulder-width apart and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the ground, then push back up to the starting position.

title: Leg Raise Oblique Crunch
desc: Perform leg raises while lying on your back with your hands behind your head. Crunch your obliques by contracting your abdominal muscles without moving your legs.

title: Landmine One Arm Bent Over Row (Version 2)
desc: This exercise targets the latissimus dorsi muscle and helps to improve overall upper body strength. It can be done with a landmine or a barbell. Standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, hold the handle of the landmine or barbell with one hand and bend your knees slightly. Keeping your back straight, lift the weight up towards the ceiling using just your one arm, then slowly lower it back down to the starting position.

title: Double Jump Rope (male)
desc: Two jump ropes rotating in opposite directions, alternately jumping in synchronization with each other.

title: Silent Burpee (female)
desc: Perform silent burpees for 5-10 minutes. Focus on maintaining proper form and technique throughout the exercise.

title: V Sit Toe Tap
desc: Perform V sit to toe taps for 3 sets of 10 reps each. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Glute Ham Twist
desc: Twist your body to target your glutes and hamstrings. Complete 3 sets of 10-15 reps

title: Prone Cervical Extension Isometric Hold

title: Landmine Press
desc: Perform 3 sets of 8-12 reps of landmine presses on a modified or heavy weight.

title: Bodyweight Svend Press
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps each of the following exercises: standing overhead press (using your bodyweight), front rack hold, side lateral raises, and rear delt flys. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Seated Chest Clam (male)
desc: Perform 12-15 reps of seated chest clams. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Lying Floor Fly
desc: Perform fly movements while lying on your back on the floor. Use a resistance band or dumbbells for added challenge.

title: Seated Sky Look (male)
desc: Perform a seated row with dumbbells while looking up towards the sky. Keep your core engaged and back straight throughout the movement.

title: Landmine Single Arm Press
desc: This exercise works multiple muscle groups at once, including the shoulders, chest, and triceps. It can be performed with either arm and is a great way to improve overall upper body strength and endurance.

title: Triceps Dip Floor (female)
desc: Perform triceps dips on the floor by lowering your body weight using your arms. Aim for 12-15 reps.

title: Seated Upper Body Rotation (female)
desc: Sit on a chair with your feet flat on the floor and hold a light dumbbell in each hand. Rotate your arms in small circles, first clockwise then counterclockwise. Repeat for 30 seconds, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 3-4 sets.

title: Seated Neck Tap (female)
desc: Gently tap your neck with a small weight or resistance band

title: Seated Behind Back Raise (female)
desc: This exercise works the lower back muscles and improves posture. Beginners should start with a slower tempo and less weight to ensure proper form.

title: Posterior Neck Isometric
desc: Sit or stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back straight. Slowly tilt your head backward, bringing your chin towards your chest. Hold for 5-10 seconds and release.

title: Jumping Single Leg Lunge
desc: Perform a single-leg lunge while jumping on the other leg. 3 sets of 12 reps.

title: Kipping Handstand Push-up
desc: Perform a handstand push-up while kipping (bending your elbows to reduce the range of motion).

title: Lateral Step-up
desc: Perform lateral steps on a step bench with one foot while holding dumbbells in both hands. Perform 12 reps for 3 sets.

title: Lateral Step-up with Knee Drive
desc: Perform lateral step-ups on a bench or box while driving one knee up towards the ceiling, alternating legs with each rep.

title: Mountain Climber Slide with Towel
desc: Perform 15 reps of mountain climbers slides, resting for 30 seconds after each set. Beginner level workout.

title: Plank Jack on Elbows
desc: Perform plank jacks by simultaneously lifting your feet off the ground and returning them to the starting position while maintaining a straight line from head to heels in a plank position. Aim for 10-15 reps per set, 3 sets total.

title: Plank Jack Slide with Towel
desc: Perform a plank position and slide your feet towards you while keeping your core engaged. Repeat for 30 seconds, 5 times.

title: Plank on Hands
desc: Hold a plank position for 30 seconds, rest for 15 seconds and repeat for 3 sets

title: Single Leg Box Jump
desc: Stand on one leg on a box and jump down and up using the other leg. Repeat for 30-60 seconds, then switch legs.

title: Single Leg Glute Bridge with External Rotation
desc: This exercise targets the glutes, hamstrings, and core muscles. It also improves balance and stability.

title: Burpee Long Jump with Push-up (male)
desc: Perform a burpee, then jump as far as possible and land in a squat position. Next, do a push-up and repeat the sequence.

title: Mountain Climber (VERSION 2) (female)
desc: This is a beginner level exercise that targets the core and legs. It involves rapidly alternating between a push-up position and a squat position, while keeping the arms close to the body.

title: Riding Outdoor Bicycle
desc: This workout is a great cardiovascular exercise that can be done by both beginners and experts. It involves riding an outdoor bicycle at a moderate pace for 30-60 minutes, with the option to increase the intensity by pedaling faster or longer distances.

title: Old School Reverse Extensions (female)
desc: Targets lower back muscles, specifically the erector spinae and latissimus dorsi. Great exercise for improving posture and reducing back pain.

title: Air Twisting Crunch (male)
desc: Perform a crunch while twisting your torso in a circular motion

title: Kneeling Staggered Push-up (female)
desc: Perform kneeling staggered push-ups with a dumbbell in each hand. Alternate arms for each rep.

title: Landmine Kneeling Thruster Press
desc: Perform kneeling thruster presses on a landmine machine with your right leg. Followed by 3 sets of 10 reps on the left leg.

title: Trap Bar Squat
desc: Perform squats using a trap bar. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and grip the bar with hands shoulder-width apart as well. Lower your body by bending at the hips and knees, keeping the torso upright. Push back up to the starting position.

desc: Perform a deadlift with one leg while holding a landmine handle in the other hand. Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the movement. Focus on squeezing your glutes and quads at the top of each rep.

title: Elevated Side Lunge
desc: Perform a side lunge on an elevated surface (step or bench) with a controlled descent and ascent. Focus on proper form and engage your core.

title: Exercise Ball Serratus Wall Slide
desc: Perform a wall slide with an exercise ball while maintaining proper form. For intermediate level, aim for 10-15 reps x 2-3 sets.

title: Burpee Push-up Mountain Climber Complex
desc: This workout is a challenging full-body exercise that combines burpees, push-ups, mountain climbers, and other exercises to provide a cardiovascular and calorie-burning workout. it's ideal for intermediate fitness level individuals who want to improve their endurance and strength.

title: Supinated Narrow Grip Pull-up
desc: This exercise works your back muscles, specifically the latissimus dorsi and biceps. Hold a bar with a supinated grip (palms facing you) and pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. As an expert, you should be able to complete 10-15 reps in 3 sets.

title: Close Grip Pull-Up
desc: Perform pull-ups with a close grip (palms facing each other).

title: Quick Feet (VERSION 2) (female)

title: Negative Push-up
desc: Perform 5-10 negative push-ups at a slow and controlled pace, focusing on lowering your body downwards with control.

title: Rear Shift Lunge from Deficit

title: Revolved Triangle Pose (female)

title: Standing Half Bend (female)
desc: Perform a half bend while standing on one leg, keeping your core engaged and your body stable.

title: Tiger Curl Pose (female)
desc: Perform a tiger curl pose on an exercise mat. Bend your knees and place your feet flat on the ground. Cross one hand over the other and bend your elbows to 90 degrees, keeping your upper arms still. Hold for 30 seconds and repeat for 3 sets.

title: Reverse Warrior Pose (female)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 8-12 reps of the reverse warrior pose, resting for 30 seconds between sets. Start with 30 seconds and gradually increase to 60 seconds as you build strength and endurance.

title: Four Limbed Staff (female)
desc: Hold each position for 30 seconds to 1 minute, resting for 30 seconds between positions.

title: 3 Leg Chatarunga Pose (female)
desc: Perform 20 reps of alternating leg 3-legged cat-cow pose. Rest for 30 seconds between sets.

title: Ladder Drill (male)
desc: Perform a ladder drill workout consisting of 10 sets of 5 reps of each exercise. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Lateral Ladder Drill (male)
desc: Perform a ladder drill with lateral movements, focusing on explosive power and speed. Complete 3-4 sets of 8-12 reps, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Plyometric Agility Drill (male)
desc: This workout involves explosive jumping and quick changes of direction, targeting agility, power, and speed. As an Expert, you should perform this exercise for 15-20 minutes.

title: Sun Salutation A (female)

title: Sun Salutation B (female)

title: 123 Back Drill (male)
desc: Perform a set of 10-15 reps of back drill exercises, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets. Focus on using proper form and technique to target the upper and middle back muscles.

title: Cone Drill (male)
desc: Perform a series of high-intensity sprints between cones placed 20-30 yards apart. Rest for 1-2 minutes between each sprint.

title: Figure Run (male)
desc: A high-intensity interval workout that combines running and strength training to improve figure fitness. Male.

title: High Hurdle Jump to Sprint and Cut (male)
desc: This high hurdle jump to sprint and cut workout is designed for experienced athletes looking to challenge themselves. The high hurdles will require proper technique and strength, while the sprinting section will test your speed and agility. Complete 3-4 rounds of the circuit, with a 1-2 minute rest between each round.

title: Partner Shuffle (male)
desc: A fun and energetic workout for couples or friends, involving partner-based movements and exercises.

title: Lay Down Push-up (male)
desc: Perform push-ups in a laying down position, with your hands under shoulders and feet flat on the ground. Aim for 5-10 reps for 5-10 minutes.

title: Low Lunge (left) (male)

title: Side Step Rear Delt Row

title: Arm Raise Step in Place (male)
desc: Step in place and raise your arms to shoulder height, then lower them back down. This exercise targets the muscles in your upper body, particularly the shoulders and triceps.

title: Arm Raise Step in Place (female)
desc: Stand with feet hip-width apart and raise arms straight out to the sides until they are at shoulder height, keeping your core engaged and legs steady. Aim for 5-10 repetitions in 3 sets.

title: Stepback Pulldown (male)
desc: This exercise targets the latissimus dorsi muscle in the upper back, as well as the biceps. It is considered an intermediate level exercise because it requires some strength and endurance to perform. To complete this workout, perform 3 sets of 8-12 reps of stepback pulldowns, resting for 30 seconds between sets.

duration.desc: 3 sets of 8-12 reps and a minute seconds rest between sets

title: Side Plank Pull (male)
desc: Perform a side plank for 30 seconds while holding a weighted pull-up bar with both hands. Rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 3 sets.

title: Punch Step Forward (female)
desc: Perform a punch step forward with your left foot, then right foot. Repeat for 5-10 minutes.

title: Lay Down Push-up (female)
desc: Perform push-ups on your laying down position with hands shoulder-width apart and lower your body until your chest almost touches the ground. Then, push yourself back to the starting position.

title: High Knee Tap (female)
desc: Perform high knee taps for 5-10 reps on each leg in a continuous motion. Complete 3 sets of the exercise.

title: Back Kick Overhead Press (female)
desc: This exercise is great for building strength and stability in the legs, glutes, and core. Beginners should start with 5-10 reps on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Back Kick Overhead Press (male)
desc: Perform a back kick overhead press by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and jumping backwards while simultaneously pressing the kettlebell overhead. Focus on proper form and use of the glutes and hamstrings to generate power.

title: Bodyweight Skipping (female)
desc: Perform skipping motions with your body weight using a jump rope. Alternate legs and arms for 20-30 reps.

title: JackKnife (male)
desc: Perform a jack knife exercise, laying on your back with your legs straight and lifting your shoulders off the ground while keeping your legs straight. This exercise will help improve your core strength and stability.

title: Pavanamuktasana Yoga Pose (male)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 5-7 reps, rest for 30 seconds in between sets.

title: Chaturanga Dandasana (Four Limbed Staff Pose) (female)
desc: Lie on your stomach with your hands under your shoulders. Press your palms into the ground, straighten your legs, and lift your chest.

title: Peacock Pose Mayurasana (female)
desc: Hold the pose for 3-5 breaths, rest for 30 seconds and repeat for 3-5 sets.

title: Bird of Paradise Pose Svarga Dvijasana (female)
desc: This is an intermediate-level yoga pose that helps to stretch and strengthen the hips, legs, and back. It also improves balance and posture.

title: Wheel Pose Urdhva Dhanurasana (female)
desc: This is an intermediate level yoga pose that strengthens the core and improves flexibility. It involves lifting the legs and arms up towards the ceiling while keeping the body in a wheel shape.

title: Two Legged Inverted Staff Pose Dwi Pada Viparita Dandasana (female)
desc: In this advanced yoga pose, the legs are inverted and held in a staff position while balancing on the hands. It requires strength, balance, and control. As an expert level workout, it is recommended to do 10-20 reps or 5-10 minutes of this exercise.

title: Dancer Pose Natarajasana (female)
desc: This standing yoga pose strengthens the hips and opens up the shoulders. Engage your core and lift your chest, keeping your spine long and straight.

title: Bodyweight Low Split Squat (male)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 8-12 bodyweight low split squats. Rest for 60-90 seconds between sets.

title: Bodyweight Slow To Explosive Squats (male)
desc: Perform bodyweight squats with slow and controlled movements for 3 sets of 8-12 reps, then gradually increase the intensity through explosive jumps for 3 sets of 6-8 reps. Rest for 1-2 minutes between sets.

title: Bodyweight Triceps Extension from Plank Position (male)
desc: Perform triceps extensions by straightening your arms from a plank position. Hold for 2-3 seconds and repeat for 10-15 reps.

title: 90 Degree Heel Touch (male)
desc: Perform heel touches while standing with your feet hip-width apart. Keep your knees straight and core engaged.

title: Yoga Vajrasana Thunderbolt Diamond Pose (male)
desc: This is an intermediate-level yoga pose that strengthens the core and improves balance. It involves lying on your back with your legs bent and feet touching, then lifting your hips off the ground and straightening your legs into a 90-degree angle.

title: Push-up Pull (male)
desc: Perform push-ups and pull-ups in a cycle of 30 seconds rest in between for 5-10 minutes.

title: Big Turn Back Stretch (female)
desc: Stretch your back and shoulders with this dynamic movement. Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, then bend forward at the hips and reach for your toes.

duration.desc: 3 sets of 3 reps (hold for 30 seconds each)

title: Handstand Hold on Wall (male)
desc: Hold a handstand against a wall for 30 seconds with proper form. This exercise is for advanced individuals, so it's recommended for experts.

title: Bear Crawl (low hip) (male)
desc: Perform a bear crawl on your hands and knees, keeping your back straight and your hips low. Move 5 yards forward and then backward, repeating for 3 sets.

title: Balance Board (female) (VERSION 2)
desc: A full-body workout that targets balance, strength, and flexibility. Includes 30 exercises with 3 levels of difficulty for each exercise.

title: Handstand Hold on Wall (female)
desc: Hold a handstand against a wall for 30 seconds, rest for 15 seconds and repeat for 3 sets. This exercise is great for building strength and endurance in the upper body, specifically in the shoulders, back, and core muscles.

title: Lying Rectus Abdominis Activation Crunch (female)
desc: lying on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor, lift shoulders off the ground, holding for a second before lowering back down

title: Lying Scalene Muscles Activation (female)
desc: This is a beginner-level workout that targets the scalene muscles in the neck and shoulders. It involves lying on your back with your arms extended overhead and slowly activating your scalene muscles using a series of contractions and releases.

title: Neck Stretch with Hand Assisted (female)
desc: Slowly tilt your head to the side and bring your ear towards your shoulder. Hold for 30 seconds and then switch sides.

title: Kneeling Sartorius Stretch (female)
desc: This exercise should be done for 5-10 minutes, with the goal of reaching your toes. it's a great way to improve flexibility in the legs and hips, especially for beginners.

title: Standing Peroneus Muscles Stretch (female)
desc: Perform the stretch for 30 seconds on each side, 2-3 times per workout.

title: Standing Foot Muscles Activation (female)
desc: This exercise targets the muscles in the feet, ankles, and calves. It helps to improve balance, posture, and overall foot health.

title: Hip Internal Rotation Test (female)
desc: Perform slow and controlled internal rotations of the legs, keeping the knees straight.

duration.desc: 3 sets of 10 reps for each leg (approximately 5-7 minutes total)

title: Thomas Test (female)
desc: This exercise targets multiple muscle groups at once and is a great all-around workout for women. It involves 3 sets of 12-15 reps of various exercises, with a minute rest between sets. For beginners, it's recommended to start with lighter weights and gradually increase the intensity as you get stronger.

title: Side and Front In Out
desc: This workout is a full-body exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, triceps, and core muscles. It involves performing side and front raises with weights, followed by an inward movement of the arms to complete the set. For an intermediate user, perform 10-15 reps for 3 sets.

title: Plank Alternate Anti Gravity Pull up
desc: Perform a standard plank position and alternate lifting one arm to perform an anti-gravity pull up for 30-60 seconds, rest for 30-60 seconds before repeating for 3 rounds.

title: Deep Push-up on Parallel Bars (male)
desc: Perform push-ups on parallel bars with your hands shoulder-width apart and lower your body until your chest nearly touches the bars.

title: Wrist Push-up (male)
desc: Perform push-ups with your wrists instead of your hands. Engage your core and lower your body until your forearms are parallel to the ground.

title: Wrist Full Push-up (male)
desc: Perform a full push-up with your wrists instead of your hands. This will engage the muscles in your forearms and help improve grip strength.

title: Inline Skating (female)
desc: Perform 3-5 sets of 2-4 minutes of moderate to high intensity inline skating. Rest for 1-2 minutes between sets.

title: Side Lying Internal Rotation (male)
desc: Lie on your side with your legs bent and feet touching. Hold a weight or resistance band in both hands at chest level. Slowly rotate your arms from internal rotation to external rotation and back to internal rotation, keeping your upper arms still and only moving your forearms.

title: Reverse Lunge High Knee Forward Lunge (male)
desc: Perform reverse lunges while bringing the knee up towards the chest on the alternate leg, then forward lunge with both legs. Aim to complete 3 sets of 8-12 reps per leg. As you get stronger, increase the number of sets or reps.

title: Bodyweight Heel Elevated Bulgarian Split Squat (male)
desc: Perform 3 sets of 10 reps on each leg with the heels elevated, focusing on proper form and range of motion.

title: Parallel Bars Bent Knee Inverted Row (male)
desc: Perform bent knee inverted rows on parallel bars with a focus on maintaining proper form and engaging the core muscles.

title: Squat Jack (male)
desc: Perform a squat followed by an immediate jump up to the desired height. Do 5-10 reps in 3 sets.

title: Jack Burpee (male)
desc: This workout is intended for experienced individuals who are looking to challenge themselves. The combination of a full-body exercise like burpees with the high-intensity interval training of mountain climbers will push your fitness to the next level.

title: Lying Single Leg Hamstring Stretch against Wall (male)
desc: This exercise is great for stretching and strengthening the hamstring muscles, which can become tight and strained from activities such as running or cycling. it's important to focus on proper form and technique to avoid injury.

title: Single Arm Lat Stretch against Wall (male)
desc: Perform a single arm lat stretch against a wall. Hold for 30-60 seconds and repeat on the other side.

title: Landmine Overhead Rear Lunge
desc: Perform a rear lunge with the barbell held overhead. Do 3 sets of 8-12 reps, resting for 60-90 seconds between sets.
